POST /v1/schemas/{org_label}/{project_label}
  {...}
The json payload:
If the @id value is found on the payload, this @id will be used. If the @id value is not found on the payload, an @id will be generated as follows: base:{UUID}. The base is the prefix defined on the resource’s project ({project_label}).
Example
Request curl -XPOST -H "Content-Type: application/json" "https://nexus.example.com/v1/schemas/myorg/myproj" -d \
'{
  "@context": [
    "https://bluebrain.github.io/nexus/contexts/shacl-20170720.json",
    {
      "this": "https://nexus.example.com/v1/schemas/myorg/myproj/e1729302-35b8-4d80-97b2-d63c984e2b5c/shapes",
      "ex": "http://example.com/"
    }
  ],
  "@id": "https://nexus.example.com/v1/resources/myorg/myproj/e1729302-35b8-4d80-97b2-d63c984e2b5c",
  "@type": "nxv:Schema",
  "shapes": [
    {
      "@id": "this:MyShape",
      "@type": "sh:NodeShape",
      "nodeKind": "sh:BlankNodeOrIRI",
      "targetClass": "ex:Custom",
      "property": [
        {
          "path": "ex:name",
          "datatype": "xsd:string",
          "minCount": 1
        },
        {
          "path": "ex:number",
